28:53.720 --> 28:56.479
What's less impressive
are our chances of survival.

28:56.560 --> 28:57.559
(AMY SCREAMS)

28:57.640 --> 29:00.239
VINCENT: Hey!
Are you looking for me, sonny?

29:01.800 --> 29:04.079
Come on! Over here.

29:04.160 --> 29:06.359
Because I'm right here waiting for you.

29:14.360 --> 29:17.159
Come on. Quickly! Get behind me.

29:17.240 --> 29:18.199
(SONIC SCREWDRIVER WHIRRS)

29:18.280 --> 29:20.839
- Doing anything?
- Uh-uh.

29:20.920 --> 29:22.679
AMY: Come on!

29:23.960 --> 29:24.919
Where is he?

29:25.000 --> 29:28.279
Where do you think he is,
you idiot? Use your head.

29:28.360 --> 29:31.039
- Anything?
- Nothing.

29:31.120 --> 29:33.039
In fact,
he seemed to rather enjoy it.

29:33.120 --> 29:35.839
- Ooh.
- (SNARLING)

29:35.920 --> 29:37.639
Duck! Left!

29:38.960 --> 29:41.159
- (AMY SCREAMS)
- Right, sorry.

29:41.240 --> 29:42.199
Agh!

29:42.280 --> 29:43.919
Your right, my left.

29:44.000 --> 29:46.319
This is no good at all.
Run like crazy and regroup.

29:46.400 --> 29:48.799
Oh, come on, in here.

30:02.680 --> 30:04.319
Right. OK.

30:04.400 --> 30:06.839
- Here's the plan. Amy, Rory...
- Who?

30:06.920 --> 30:08.879
Sorry, um, Vincent.

30:08.960 --> 30:10.879
- What is the plan?
- I don't know, actually.

30:10.960 --> 30:12.239
My only definite plan is that in future,

30:12.320 --> 30:14.159
I'm just using this screwdriver
for screwing in screws.

30:14.240 --> 30:16.679
Give me a second. I'll be back.

30:17.760 --> 30:20.519
- I suppose we could try talking to him.
- Talking to him?!

30:20.600 --> 30:22.959
Well, yes. Might be interesting
to know his side of the story.

30:23.040 --> 30:23.999
(ROARING)

30:24.080 --> 30:27.519
Yes, though maybe he's not really
in the mood for conversation

30:27.600 --> 30:29.279
right at this precise moment.

30:29.360 --> 30:31.399
(BANGING AND GROWLING)

30:33.120 --> 30:36.799
Well, no harm trying. Listen.
Listen!

30:38.800 --> 30:40.439
I know you can understand me.

30:40.560 --> 30:44.879
Even though I know you won't
understand whyyou can understand me.

30:45.000 --> 30:49.239
I also know that no-one's talked to you
for a pretty long stretch,

30:49.320 --> 30:52.719
but please...listen.

30:54.960 --> 30:57.679
I also don't belong on this planet.

30:57.760 --> 31:01.239
I also am...alone.

31:02.320 --> 31:06.199
If you trust me, I'm sure
we can come to some kind of, you know,

31:06.280 --> 31:07.839
understanding.

31:07.920 --> 31:11.559
And then... And then, who knows?

31:11.640 --> 31:13.879
(SHATTERING)

31:17.200 --> 31:20.799
(ROARING)

31:22.160 --> 31:23.639
Over here, mate!

31:25.320 --> 31:26.999
What's it up to now?

31:27.080 --> 31:30.159
It's moving round the room.
Feeling its way around.

31:32.120 --> 31:35.079
- What?
- It's like it's trapped.

31:35.160 --> 31:38.159
It's moving round
the edges of the room.

31:39.720 --> 31:42.639
AMY: I can't see a thing.

31:44.200 --> 31:46.119
I am really stupid.

31:46.200 --> 31:49.799
Oh, get a grip! This is not a moment
to re-evaluate your self-esteem.

31:49.880 --> 31:54.279
No, I am really stupid
and I'm growing old.

31:54.360 --> 31:56.799
Why does it attack,
but never eat its victims?

31:56.880 --> 31:59.319
And why was it abandoned by its pack
and left here to die?

31:59.400 --> 32:04.519
And why is it feeling its way helplessly
around the walls of the room?

32:04.600 --> 32:07.199
It can't see, it's blind.

32:07.280 --> 32:09.599
And that, of course, explains
why it has such perfect hearing!

32:09.680 --> 32:12.199
Which unfortunately also
explains why it is now

32:12.280 --> 32:14.799
turning around
and heading straight for us.

32:14.880 --> 32:16.839
Vincent. Vincent, what's happening?

32:16.920 --> 32:19.679
