32:46.560 --> 32:49.399
I only meant to wound it,
I never meant to...

32:49.480 --> 32:51.679
(GURGLING)

32:51.760 --> 32:53.399
He's trying to say something.

32:55.000 --> 32:56.839
What is it?

32:56.920 --> 33:00.399
I'm having trouble making it out,
but I think he's saying,

33:00.480 --> 33:04.359
"I'm afraid. I'm afraid."

33:08.480 --> 33:10.119
There, there.

33:10.200 --> 33:11.479
Ssh! Ssh!

33:11.560 --> 33:15.519
It's OK. It's OK. You'll be fine. Ssh!

33:18.560 --> 33:21.639
(SIGHS)

33:26.440 --> 33:28.959
He was frightened.

33:29.040 --> 33:30.799
And he lashed out

33:30.880 --> 33:35.119
like humans, who lash out
when they're frightened.

33:35.200 --> 33:37.399
Like the villagers who scream at me.

33:38.960 --> 33:41.519
Like the children
who throw stones at me.

33:43.400 --> 33:47.759
You know, sometimes winning -
winning is no fun at all.

34:06.720 --> 34:08.559
Hold my hand, Doctor.

34:10.560 --> 34:13.479
Try to see what I see.

34:13.560 --> 34:17.639
We are so lucky we are still alive
to see this beautiful world.

34:17.720 --> 34:19.159
Look at the sky.

34:19.240 --> 34:23.999
It's not dark and black
and without character.

34:24.080 --> 34:26.119
The black is in fact deep blue.

34:26.200 --> 34:29.279
And over there, lighter blue.

34:29.360 --> 34:32.119
And blowing through
the blueness and the blackness,

34:32.200 --> 34:34.399
the wind swirling through the air

34:34.480 --> 34:38.359
and then shining, burning,
bursting through - the stars!

34:38.440 --> 34:40.759
Can you see
how they roar their light?

34:42.400 --> 34:44.759
Everywhere we look,

34:44.840 --> 34:49.079
the complex magic of nature
blazes before our eyes.

34:51.640 --> 34:54.319
I've seen many things, my friend.

34:54.400 --> 34:55.799
But you're right.

34:57.800 --> 35:02.399
Nothing quite as wonderful
as the things you see.

35:11.280 --> 35:13.559
I will miss you terribly.

35:26.320 --> 35:28.959
